= Smidig 2009 Conference site

== Recommended tools

=== Windows

* "Ruby installer":http://www.ruby-lang.org/en/downloads/
* "TortoiseSVN":http://tortoisesvn.net/downloads
* "e TextEditor":http://www.e-texteditor.com/
* "Subversion command line binaries":http://www.collab.net/downloads/subversion/


== Getting started

<code>
Check out the code from http://svn.smidig.no/smidig2009/
Install Ruby
gem update --system
gem install rails --version=2.3.2 
gem install sqlite3-ruby --version=1.2.3
ON WINDOWS: Grab sqlite DLL from http://www.sqlite.org/download.html and stuff it in c:\ruby\bin.
rake gems:install
rake db:populate (calls db:migrate)
rake test
ruby script/server
http://localhost:3000
</code>


== Checking in

You need a user in the subversion repository.
Use this procedure to create or change your password:

<code>
ssh to smidig_no@svn.smidig.no
htpasswd ~/svn/smidig2009.passwd <your username>
* Enter your desired password when prompted
vim ~/svn/smidig2009.access
* Add a line with "<your username> = rw"
</code>


== Deploying new version to staging environment

<code>
gem install net-ssh net-scp
svn commit
rake dreamhost:staging
(if database was changed) rake dreamhost:staging:migrate
</code>

== Deploying new version to all environment

Use this if you only have minor changes:

<code>
svn commit
rake dreamhost:all
</code>
